<title type="html"><![CDATA[Only 64 sprites!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=29&amp;p=133#p133"><![CDATA[
If you do a mid-frame sprite DMA, there can be more than 64 sprites.  But the screen has to be turned off for maybe 5 scanlines or so, there'd be limitations with sorting and positioning, etc.  It could be possible though, to use all the sprite tiles in one frame, heheh.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Nov 12, 2004 5:38 pm</p><hr />
